        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Calibrachoa irgangiana: A. Habit; B--C. Flowers showing the prominent anthers (yellow) of the longest pair of stamens opening at the mouth of corolla tube. Calibrachoa longistyla: D. Habit; E. Corolla in frontal view showing the prominent style opening above the anthers of the longest stamens; F. Flower in side view showing the five stamens and the style. Photographs by J.R. Stehmann (A–E) and J.A. Greppi (F)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4918520/files/figure.png" .

